cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC

This paper is about learning word embeddings for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel neural network architecture for this purpose, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of morphological knowledge to improve word embeddings, which could be considered a form of feature engineering (cs.CC) and involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) to refine the knowledge.
